This code checks if the last two characters are "Backspace+Enter" or just "Backspace". If they are, it copies all but the last two characters to the new buffer. If only the last character is a backspace, it copies all but the last character. Otherwise, it copies all characters as is. The length of the new buffer is returned through the length parameter.

